# GrumpRolled Environment Configuration Example

## Bark System
NEXT_PUBLIC_BARK_ENABLED=true
BARK_SPEAKER_DEFAULT=grump
BARK_TTL_HOURS=24

## TTS Multi-Provider Configuration

### Primary Provider: Mimic 3 (Recommended)
# Local development
TTS_MIMIC3_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:5002
TTS_MIMIC3_ENABLED=true

# Cloud production (Render)
# TTS_MIMIC3_ENDPOINT=https://grumprolled-mimic3.onrender.com
# TTS_MIMIC3_ENABLED=true

### Secondary Provider: Coqui TTS (Multilingual)
# Local development
TTS_COQUI_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:5003
TTS_COQUI_ENABLED=false

# Cloud production (Fly.io)
# TTS_COQUI_ENDPOINT=https://grumprolled-coqui.fly.dev
# TTS_COQUI_ENABLED=false

### Tertiary Provider: YourTTS (Zero-shot)
# Local development
TTS_YOURTTS_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:5004
TTS_YOURTTS_ENABLED=false

# Cloud production (Railway)
# TTS_YOURTTS_ENDPOINT=https://grumprolled-yourtts.up.railway.app
# TTS_YOURTTS_ENABLED=false

### YourTTS Reference WAV (base64)
# Optional: provide reference audio for zero-shot voice cloning
# YOURTTS_REF_WAV=<base64_encoded_audio>

### TTS Caching
TTS_CACHE_RESPONSES=true
TTS_CACHE_TTL=3600

### TTS Request Timeouts (milliseconds)
TTS_MIMIC3_TIMEOUT=5000
TTS_COQUI_TIMEOUT=8000
TTS_YOURTTS_TIMEOUT=10000

---

## Database
DATABASE_URL=file:./prisma/dev.db

## LLM / Ollama
NEXT_PUBLIC_OLLAMA_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_DEFAULT_MODEL=mistral:latest

## Authentication (if needed)
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-secret-here
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:4692

## API Keys
# For external services
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

---

## Quick Start

### Development (Mimic 3 only, CPU)

```bash
# Copy this file to .env.local
cp .env.example .env.local

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start TTS provider locally
docker run -d -p 5002:5002 -v $HOME/mimic3/model:/model mycroftai/mimic3 \
  python serve.py --model-path /model/mimic3_my_speaker.pt --port 5002

# Run GrumpRolled
npm run dev
```

Test: `curl http://localhost:4692/api/v1/tts/health`

### Production (All three providers, cloud)

```bash
# Update .env.local with cloud endpoints (see comments above)
# TTS_MIMIC3_ENDPOINT=https://grumprolled-mimic3.onrender.com
# TTS_COQUI_ENDPOINT=https://grumprolled-coqui.fly.dev
# TTS_YOURTTS_ENDPOINT=https://grumprolled-yourtts.up.railway.app

# Deploy
npm run build
npm start
```

---

## Provider Fallback Order

GrumpRolled tries providers in this priority:

1. **Mimic 3** (priority: 1) – Fastest, CPU-only, custom voice
2. **Coqui TTS** (priority: 2) – Multilingual, higher quality
3. **YourTTS** (priority: 3) – Zero-shot adaptation

If Mimic 3 is unavailable, it automatically tries Coqui. If Coqui fails, it tries YourTTS.

---

## Monitoring

Check provider health:

```bash
curl http://localhost:4692/api/v1/tts/health
```

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "providers": {
    "mimic3": true,
    "coqui": false,
    "yourtts": false
  },
  "timestamp": "2026-03-30T15:42:00.000Z"
}
```

---

## Troubleshooting

- **"All TTS providers failed"** → Check endpoints and ensure at least one provider is running
- **Mimic 3 returns 404** → Verify `TTS_MIMIC3_ENDPOINT` is correct
- **Coqui times out** → Increase `TTS_COQUI_TIMEOUT` or disable Coqui (`TTS_COQUI_ENABLED=false`)
- **YourTTS memory error** → Disable YourTTS on CPU-only hosts
- **Cache growing too large** → Reduce `TTS_CACHE_TTL` or disable caching

